  "body": "Right now it's clumsy if the user wants to have a routing rule that matches and then sends traffic to a number of upstream clusters on a % basis. We should support this directly both via static percentages as well as runtime override of the percentages.\r\n\r\nThe rule might look something like:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\n...\r\n\"weighted_clusters:\" [\r\n  { \"name\": \"cluster1\", \"weight\": 33 },\r\n  { \"name\": \"cluster2\", \"weight\": 33 },\r\n  { \"name\": \"cluster3\", \"weight\": 33 },\r\n]\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nNeed to also specify what the rule would look like with runtime overrides. Open so to suggestions here. \r\n\r\ncc @rshriram ",
